What is this ArgumentOutOfRangeException?

In C#, methods generally operate by taking external parameters. These parameters typically have a logical "expected range".
If the value you send to a method is outside the acceptable limits defined for that method to function, 
the program stops executing and tells you: "I cannot work with this rgument you gave me,
because it is out of my bounds!" This is exactly when an ArgumentOutOfRangeException is thrown.

string word = "Yazılım"; // A 7-character word. Indexes range from 0 to 6.

// The Substring method requires a starting index and the number of characters to retrieve.
// We are telling it: "Start from the 10th index and bring me 2 characters."
string part = word.Substring(10, 2);
